Merrill Moves Fallon to Senior Financial Sales Job in Singapore

-- B y   B e i   H u
-- 
2011-02-23T03:21:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/merrill-moves-fallon-to-senior-financial-sales-job-in-singapore.html
James Fallon is relocated to
Singapore from  Hong Kong  to take the senior financing sales role
at  Bank of America Corp .’s Merrill Lynch prime brokerage
business, according to an internal memo obtained by Bloomberg
News.  Fallon, who joined Bank of America Merrill Lynch in May
2009 from Tremont Capital Management, will be contributing to
the firm’s capital introductions efforts in Singapore, the memo
said. Fallon will report to Dan McNicholas, the firm’s head of
Asia Pacific Financing Sales, and John Hui, head of Southeast
Asia Equity Sales, it said.  Chia-peck Wong, a Hong Kong-based spokeswoman, confirmed
the content of the memo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bei Hu in Hong Kong at 
 bhu5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tomoko Yamazaki at 
 tyamazaki@bloomberg.net  